# Deploy Totem Edge SDK Docs on a Fresh Replit Project

This folder contains a fully self-contained static build of the Totem Edge SDK documentation site.
No monorepo dependencies, TypeScript sources, or workspace packages are needed on the destination —
only the pre-built `build/` directory and `server.js` are required at runtime.

## Three steps to serve on Replit

1. `npm install`        — installs Docusaurus, TypeDoc, and all build tooling (see package.json).
                          Only `serve-handler` is needed at *runtime*; the rest are build-time only.
2. `node server.js`     — starts the HTTP server on $PORT (Replit sets this automatically)
3. Done.               — open the Webview tab to see the docs

> **Tip:** If you only want to *serve* an already-built `build/` folder (no rebuild needed),
> you can run `npm install --production` to install just `serve-handler`, then `node server.js`.

## Changing the domain

All site identity (name, url, baseUrl, tagline, analytics IDs) lives in `site.config.json`
at the root of the TotemEdgeSDKDocs source folder. Moving to a new domain is a one-file change —
edit `site.config.json`, re-run `pnpm run docs:build`, and re-deploy.

## Rebuilding

Rebuilding requires the full Axia monorepo (for TypeDoc source access):

```bash
# From the monorepo root:
pnpm run docs       # generate static files (llms.txt, docs-manifest.json)
pnpm run docs:build # full Docusaurus production build → build/
# The resulting TotemEdgeSDKDocs/build/ folder is what you copy here.
```

## Keeping llms.txt current

`static/llms.txt`, `static/llms-full.txt`, and `static/docs-manifest.json` are regenerated on
every `pnpm run docs`. Copy the updated files alongside `build/` when deploying a new version.
